# ORIG TITLE    Bowie exhibition breaks record in London . 
# ORIG CONTENT  David Bowie has broken box office records with a new exhibition dedicated to his long and innovative career. It features more than 300 objects celebrating his lyrics, costumes, films and stage sets. 50,000 advance tickets have been sold for “David bowie is.” which runs from March 23 to August 11 at London’s Victoria and Albert Museum and the organisers say there are still more tickets available. The exhibition coincides with the release of the 66-year-old’s new album “The Next Day” which shot to number one in a number of charts around the world. 
